      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What makes turmeric gummies effective for inflammation?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The active compound in turmeric is curcumin, which inhibits NF-kB, a transcription factor that activates genes involved in inflammation. Curcumin also suppresses COX-2 and LOX enzymes, the same targets as ibuprofen and aspirin, but through a different mechanism. A 2016 systematic review in the Journal of Medicinal Food analyzed 8 randomized controlled trials and concluded that curcumin at doses of 1000mg per day significantly reduced markers of systemic inflammation including C-reactive protein (CRP) and interleukin-6 (IL-6). The challenge with turmeric gummies is bioavailability — curcumin is poorly absorbed without an absorption enhancer like piperine or a lipid-based delivery system.' },
