    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the difference between turmeric and curcumin?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Turmeric is the whole spice derived from the Curcuma longa plant root, commonly used in cooking and responsible for the yellow color in curry. Curcumin is the primary bioactive compound within turmeric, comprising approximately 3% of turmeric powder by weight. Curcuminoids — curcumin, demethoxycurcumin, and bisdemethoxycurcumin — are the compounds responsible for the anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and therapeutic properties attributed to turmeric. Standardized turmeric extracts concentrate curcuminoids to 95%, delivering roughly 30 times more active compound per milligram than raw turmeric powder.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How long does it take for turmeric gummies to work?',
